This paper is about learning-to-rank from implicit feedback in search engines and recommender systems, which is a topic that falls under the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a new model for examination bias estimation that takes into account context, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of Inverse Propensity Score (IPS) weighting techniques to address selection biases and missing data is also relevant to causal inference (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, and cs.SI.
